verbose_text: His laboratory investigations revealed high levels of free thyroxine (FT4) with a suppressed thyroid stimulating hormone (TSH) level (FT4 33.5 pmol/L, nv 10.3-24.4; FT3 8.7 pmol/L, nv 2.7-6.4; TSH 0.004 mUI/L, nv 0.04-0.4), anti-TSH receptor antibody positivity (2.7 U/L, nv < 1.75) and anti-Tg-A and anti-TPO negativity.
